1
00:00:00,002 --> 00:00:03,149
Previously on AMC’s Hell on Wheels…

2
00:00:03,175 --> 00:00:05,668
- She soot a man.
- You are the law.

3
00:00:05,694 --> 00:00:08,097
You arrest the church lady
for shooting Sidney Snow.

4
00:00:08,123 --> 00:00:10,550
Sidney's bleeding out.
He needs a doctor.

5
00:00:11,690 --> 00:00:15,104
In the event he dies first, it must be
seen that she's held accountable.

6
00:00:15,130 --> 00:00:17,485
This here is "Dandy" Johnny Shea.

7
00:00:17,511 --> 00:00:19,253
And from this day forward,

8
00:00:19,279 --> 00:00:22,011
he is the new proprietor
of this establishment.

9
00:00:22,224 --> 00:00:24,169
He's dead, isn't he?

10
00:00:26,454 --> 00:00:28,189
I'll figure a way out.

11
00:00:33,673 --> 00:00:38,319
You do swear by almighty God,
the searcher of all hearts,

12
00:00:38,347 --> 00:00:41,124
that the evidence you
give shall be the truth,

13
00:00:41,159 --> 00:00:42,726
the whole truth,

14
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:44,764
and nothing but the truth,

15
00:00:44,800 --> 00:00:47,608
as you shall answer to
God on the last great day?

16
00:01:10,503 --> 00:01:14,574
In the matter of the United
States versus Ruth Cole,

17
00:01:14,609 --> 00:01:18,919
the defendant stands
accused of unlawfully, feloniously,

18
00:01:18,954 --> 00:01:23,931
and of malice aforethought
shooting into Sidney snow

19
00:01:23,965 --> 00:01:27,002
two mortal wounds of which he died,

20
00:01:27,036 --> 00:01:29,173
contrary to the law, peace,

21
00:01:29,208 --> 00:01:33,546
and dignity of the Wyoming territory.

22
00:01:33,581 --> 00:01:36,384
Having heard these charges, what say you?

23
00:01:47,005 --> 00:01:48,739
Guilty.

24
00:01:54,780 --> 00:01:58,988
Miss Cole,

25
00:01:59,030 --> 00:02:01,302
in my hand,

26
00:02:01,336 --> 00:02:04,007
a written statement by
head of Railroad Police,

27
00:02:04,041 --> 00:02:06,411
Cullen Bohannon.

28
00:02:06,445 --> 00:02:09,982
He says you aided and
protected an officer of the law

29
00:02:10,016 --> 00:02:12,019
from an armed felon.

30
00:02:12,053 --> 00:02:14,924
This would not only prove you innocent,

31
00:02:14,958 --> 00:02:18,930
but mean you saved a life, if not several.

32
00:02:18,964 --> 00:02:23,370
Now, this court asks a second time.

33
00:02:23,404 --> 00:02:26,142
What say you?

34
00:02:26,177 --> 00:02:27,812
I say I am guilty.

35
00:02:27,846 --> 00:02:30,015
Ruth, don't do this.

36
00:02:30,049 --> 00:02:32,051
- Ruth.
- Order, sir.

37
00:02:34,556 --> 00:02:38,963
Miss Cole, it is unclear to
me whether you're of fit mind

38
00:02:38,997 --> 00:02:41,400
to defend yourself.

39
00:02:41,435 --> 00:02:43,636
I move for a continuance to afford miss Cole

40
00:02:43,671 --> 00:02:46,407
time to acquire proper counsel.

41
00:02:46,442 --> 00:02:50,248
I murdered that man, Governor.

42
00:02:50,283 --> 00:02:54,056
Not out of fear, nor aiding the law,

43
00:02:54,090 --> 00:02:56,862
but for no purpose other
than to end the man's life

44
00:02:56,898 --> 00:02:59,700
who took my son's.

45
00:02:59,734 --> 00:03:02,301
I am guilty. I have pled so.

46
00:03:07,374 --> 00:03:08,774
Mm.

47
00:03:13,781 --> 00:03:18,118
You, Ruth Elizabeth Cole,

48
00:03:18,152 --> 00:03:20,920
are guilty of murder

49
00:03:20,954 --> 00:03:24,424
and shall be hanged by the neck
until you are dead tomorrow.

50
00:03:24,458 --> 00:03:26,093
[Crowd murmuring]

51
00:03:26,127 --> 00:03:29,460
May God have mercy upon your soul.

52
00:03:29,494 --> 00:03:31,095
[Gavel bangs]

53
00:03:34,633 --> 00:03:37,598
[Western folk music]

54
00:03:37,632 --> 00:03:38,132
♪ ♪

55
00:04:06,355 --> 00:04:09,324
Have the gallows constructed
in the town square.

56
00:04:09,359 --> 00:04:10,893
A public execution?

57
00:04:10,927 --> 00:04:12,962
Transparency, judge,

58
00:04:12,996 --> 00:04:15,668
followed by a strict adherence to the law.

59
00:04:15,702 --> 00:04:17,503
A death warrant should be drawn up.

60
00:04:17,537 --> 00:04:19,070
Do it.

61
00:04:19,105 --> 00:04:20,571
No mistakes.

62
00:04:20,605 --> 00:04:22,239
You got nothing to gain by this.

63
00:04:22,273 --> 00:04:26,143
I gave miss Cole every
opportunity to acquit herself.

64
00:04:26,177 --> 00:04:29,148
Her refusal to do so means
that justice must be served.

65
00:04:29,182 --> 00:04:32,251
Hanging a grieving mother,
that don't serve nobody.

66
00:04:32,286 --> 00:04:35,755
Neither does allowing a
confessed murderer to walk free.

67
00:04:35,790 --> 00:04:39,490
No one is above the law,
not even a church lady.

68
00:04:39,524 --> 00:04:41,593
Then pardon her.
You got that power as governor.

69
00:04:41,628 --> 00:04:43,063
I do,

70
00:04:43,097 --> 00:04:45,764
but a pardon must be affirmatively accepted

71
00:04:45,799 --> 00:04:49,504
by the guilty party to be
recognized by the courts.

72
00:04:49,539 --> 00:04:50,874
The woman in that courtroom

73
00:04:50,908 --> 00:04:54,911
did not appear interested in clemency.

74
00:04:54,945 --> 00:04:58,351
I get her to accept a pardon,
you'll sign it?

75
00:04:58,386 --> 00:05:01,221
With pleasure.

76
00:05:01,255 --> 00:05:03,560
The law requires the noose go on tomorrow.

77
00:05:26,385 --> 00:05:30,491
All right, keep your guilty plea.

78
00:05:30,526 --> 00:05:32,894
Take your stand.

79
00:05:32,928 --> 00:05:34,829
Then you'll accept a
pardon from the governor.

80
00:05:34,864 --> 00:05:36,432
The governor hasn't pardoned me.

81
00:05:36,466 --> 00:05:38,332
He'll give you one. He told me so hisself.

82
00:05:38,367 --> 00:05:42,265
I never asked for that.

83
00:05:42,299 --> 00:05:43,498
Hanged by the neck until dead.

84
00:05:43,532 --> 00:05:44,999
Did you hear him in there?

85
00:05:45,025 --> 00:05:49,358
Pardons are for cowards like Sidney snow.

86
00:05:52,604 --> 00:05:55,574
Taking a pardon,

87
00:05:55,609 --> 00:05:57,813
that ain't a coward's choice.

88
00:05:57,847 --> 00:05:59,181
Dying is.

89
00:05:59,215 --> 00:06:02,151
Either way, the choice is mine.

90
00:06:02,186 --> 00:06:04,089
And my choice is no.

91
00:06:11,767 --> 00:06:14,735
[Piano music playing]

92
00:06:14,770 --> 00:06:15,270
♪ ♪

93
00:06:39,997 --> 00:06:43,302
My father was a judge.

94
00:06:43,337 --> 00:06:46,305
After a bad ruling,

95
00:06:46,340 --> 00:06:51,177
well,
he'd sneak out and take my mother dancing.

96
00:06:51,211 --> 00:06:53,912
Do you waltz?

97
00:06:53,947 --> 00:06:56,913
I haven't come to dance, John.

98
00:06:56,948 --> 00:06:58,915
Come on.

99
00:06:58,950 --> 00:07:02,253
It's simple.

100
00:07:02,287 --> 00:07:06,722
A waltz requires a man to lead.

101
00:07:06,757 --> 00:07:09,026
I've never excelled in that arena.

102
00:07:11,729 --> 00:07:14,399
I've come for comment on the kangaroo court

103
00:07:14,433 --> 00:07:16,333
you authorized on your arrival

104
00:07:16,367 --> 00:07:20,736
and your acquisition of McGinnes'
casino thereafter.

105
00:07:20,770 --> 00:07:23,872
Ancient history, miss Ellison.

106
00:07:23,907 --> 00:07:27,409
I prefer to call it context.

107
00:07:27,443 --> 00:07:31,214
This is the story I won't like?

108
00:07:31,248 --> 00:07:33,618
It starts and ends with a
federally-approved hanging.

109
00:07:37,090 --> 00:07:40,561
I extended miss Cole a pardon.

110
00:07:40,595 --> 00:07:44,865
If she should refuse,
that would be her decision.

111
00:07:44,899 --> 00:07:46,732
Mr. snow's appointment to marshal,

112
00:07:46,767 --> 00:07:48,700
I suppose that was her decision as well?

113
00:07:48,735 --> 00:07:51,740
And his subsequent burning of her church.

114
00:07:51,774 --> 00:07:54,943
We are all complicit, John.

115
00:07:54,977 --> 00:07:56,779
Men with power and money are guilty,

116
00:07:56,813 --> 00:07:59,783
while a woman with no currency
except her own convictions

117
00:07:59,818 --> 00:08:01,050
is set to hang.

118
00:08:01,084 --> 00:08:04,287
Burn this city down,

119
00:08:04,322 --> 00:08:07,059
you'll have no friends left but the ashes.

120
00:08:07,093 --> 00:08:10,598
Exactly as much as Ruth Cole.

121
00:08:10,632 --> 00:08:14,134
You'll cast her as some Saint?

122
00:08:14,168 --> 00:08:16,537
I'm still deciding on the devil.

123
00:08:21,713 --> 00:08:24,851
Come on, ain't got time to waste.

124
00:08:24,886 --> 00:08:26,851
Train leaves in five minutes.

125
00:08:26,885 --> 00:08:27,919
Train?

126
00:08:27,954 --> 00:08:29,957
For New York.

127
00:08:29,991 --> 00:08:34,162
Mary, my first wife,
still got folks in the city.

128
00:08:34,196 --> 00:08:35,532
I sent them a telegram.

129
00:08:35,567 --> 00:08:37,336
They said you could stay with them

130
00:08:37,370 --> 00:08:39,007
till you get back on your feet.

131
00:08:39,041 --> 00:08:40,509
I'm not going to New York.

132
00:08:40,543 --> 00:08:42,479
Yes, you are.

133
00:08:42,513 --> 00:08:44,316
I'm putting you on that train.

134
00:08:44,350 --> 00:08:46,018
You're putting this behind you.

135
00:08:46,053 --> 00:08:48,013
I won't be a fugitive from the law.

136
00:08:48,022 --> 00:08:49,990
No one will come after you.

137
00:08:50,024 --> 00:08:51,624
You'll disappear.

138
00:08:51,659 --> 00:08:55,328
That'll be that. You can start fresh.

139
00:08:55,362 --> 00:08:57,029
The only life I have is here.

140
00:08:57,063 --> 00:08:58,797
Yeah, I thought that once in Mississippi.

141
00:08:58,831 --> 00:09:00,365
Train ride changed all that.

142
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,967
I intend to stay and accept

143
00:09:02,001 --> 00:09:03,701
the consequences for what I've done.

144
00:09:03,736 --> 00:09:06,404
You'll stay, and you'll die. And for what?

145
00:09:06,437 --> 00:09:08,437
Teach everybody some lesson
about right and wrong?

146
00:09:08,471 --> 00:09:11,706
It's not your responsibility to save me,
Mr. Bohannon.

147
00:09:11,741 --> 00:09:13,108
You're getting on that train.

148
00:09:13,142 --> 00:09:14,745
- I've made my decision.
- Yeah?

149
00:09:14,780 --> 00:09:16,281
Well, I just unmade it.

150
00:09:16,316 --> 00:09:18,784
What? No, no. [Stammering]

151
00:09:18,819 --> 00:09:20,319
Let me go.

152
00:09:20,353 --> 00:09:22,653
- Come on, you're leaving.
- No.

153
00:09:22,687 --> 00:09:23,654
No!

154
00:09:23,689 --> 00:09:25,825
I was ready to leave

155
00:09:25,859 --> 00:09:27,594
after Sean died.

156
00:09:27,629 --> 00:09:30,229
I was ready to go back to Omaha with Ezra.

157
00:09:30,263 --> 00:09:32,197
You asked me to stay.

158
00:09:35,466 --> 00:09:37,702
And I stayed for you.

159
00:09:41,276 --> 00:09:44,178
This time, I stay for me.

160
00:09:52,129 --> 00:09:53,763
Bohannon.

161
00:09:55,787 --> 00:09:57,422
Bohannon.

162
00:10:03,061 --> 00:10:06,331
Delaney is quite capable
of putting the final pieces

163
00:10:06,365 --> 00:10:09,199
in place if you need to be somewhere else.

164
00:10:09,234 --> 00:10:11,632
I'm right where I need to be.

165
00:10:11,667 --> 00:10:17,070
[Grunting]

166
00:10:17,105 --> 00:10:18,539
Son of a bitch.

167
00:10:23,540 --> 00:10:28,541
When we lost my only son to cholera,
I was away working.

168
00:10:30,277 --> 00:10:34,310
Do you know where I was
and what I was doing?

169
00:10:34,344 --> 00:10:37,173
No.

170
00:10:37,208 --> 00:10:38,940
Neither do I.

171
00:10:43,776 --> 00:10:46,377
There ain't nothing I can do for Ruth.

172
00:10:46,411 --> 00:10:50,383
The thing to do is be with her.

173
00:10:53,555 --> 00:10:56,356
[Train whistle blows]

174
00:11:19,550 --> 00:11:21,470
The church lady's not gonna hang.

175
00:11:34,726 --> 00:11:37,863
The casino you can keep.

176
00:11:37,897 --> 00:11:40,297
But if you think you can prevent
me from enforcing the law

177
00:11:40,298 --> 00:11:44,302
through intimidation,
you haven't been paying attention.

178
00:11:45,737 --> 00:11:49,472
If Ruth Cole sees an early grave,

179
00:11:49,506 --> 00:11:52,275
you best be digging too.

180
00:11:52,309 --> 00:11:55,545
She refused my pardon offer.

181
00:11:55,579 --> 00:11:57,548
There's nothing else I can do.

182
00:11:57,582 --> 00:11:59,452
You'll find a way.

183
00:12:07,364 --> 00:12:08,931
I'm sure of it.

184
00:12:32,145 --> 00:12:33,812
Step aside.

185
00:12:41,226 --> 00:12:44,227
[Grunting]

186
00:13:04,734 --> 00:13:07,701
[Melancholy music]

187
00:13:07,736 --> 00:13:08,236
♪ ♪

188
00:13:17,730 --> 00:13:18,230
♪ ♪

189
00:13:30,237 --> 00:13:30,737
♪ ♪

190
00:13:41,313 --> 00:13:41,813
♪ ♪

191
00:13:52,315 --> 00:13:52,815
♪ ♪

192
00:14:05,925 --> 00:14:06,425
♪ ♪

193
00:14:11,764 --> 00:14:13,724
Why don't you go get a drink, Dutch?

194
00:14:27,214 --> 00:14:30,181
I couldn't sleep.

195
00:14:30,207 --> 00:14:32,174
Me neither.

196
00:14:40,495 --> 00:14:43,396
Would you do anything different

197
00:14:45,765 --> 00:14:47,799
if you could go back?

198
00:14:50,771 --> 00:14:53,773
[Hammering]

199
00:14:59,246 --> 00:15:04,418
I would be a better husband,

200
00:15:04,452 --> 00:15:08,389
a better father.

201
00:15:08,423 --> 00:15:12,391
I would be more patient with Ezra.

202
00:15:12,425 --> 00:15:14,594
[Chuckles]

203
00:15:14,629 --> 00:15:18,002
They don't get more patient than you.

204
00:15:18,036 --> 00:15:20,672
Boy didn't make it easy on you,

205
00:15:20,706 --> 00:15:23,575
setting fires,

206
00:15:23,610 --> 00:15:26,115
rustling horses,

207
00:15:26,149 --> 00:15:30,490
kicking frogs.

208
00:15:30,524 --> 00:15:33,661
What I would give for
a church full of frogs.

209
00:15:38,636 --> 00:15:42,670
I'd let the both of you go to Omaha.

210
00:15:42,705 --> 00:15:44,402
I don't blame you.

211
00:15:54,180 --> 00:15:56,347
I would kill Sidney snow.

212
00:16:02,385 --> 00:16:04,485
So would I.

213
00:16:26,235 --> 00:16:29,373
After the war,

214
00:16:29,407 --> 00:16:33,410
I found myself walking the streets of D.C.

215
00:16:33,452 --> 00:16:38,090
What were you doing in D.C.?

216
00:16:38,116 --> 00:16:42,187
There was this crowd
outside a federal building.

217
00:16:42,221 --> 00:16:45,191
Political rally, I thought.

218
00:16:45,225 --> 00:16:50,094
Some senator speaking on national unity.

219
00:16:53,867 --> 00:16:58,472
Come to realize it wasn't a rally.

220
00:17:00,575 --> 00:17:03,875
It was a execution.

221
00:17:03,910 --> 00:17:05,442
They march this poor bastard out

222
00:17:05,476 --> 00:17:10,410
and read him his rights.

223
00:17:12,246 --> 00:17:14,881
I swear, it felt no different than

224
00:17:14,915 --> 00:17:16,082
you and me talking right now.

225
00:17:16,116 --> 00:17:18,916
Civilized, even.

226
00:17:20,651 --> 00:17:24,016
But his...

227
00:17:24,050 --> 00:17:27,451
His neck didn't snap right, and...

228
00:17:31,220 --> 00:17:36,888
We spent ten minutes

229
00:17:38,957 --> 00:17:42,892
just watching him choke.

230
00:17:42,927 --> 00:17:45,428
I know what you're doing.

231
00:17:45,462 --> 00:17:48,898
Piss ran down his leg at five minutes in.

232
00:17:51,635 --> 00:17:55,241
The shit come at eight.

233
00:17:55,276 --> 00:17:58,813
The worst part was the
popping sound his neck made.

234
00:17:58,848 --> 00:18:03,485
It was like a firecracker
on the fourth of July.

235
00:18:06,989 --> 00:18:10,927
And there I am,

236
00:18:10,961 --> 00:18:14,133
in the nation's capital,

237
00:18:14,168 --> 00:18:17,467
watching this...

238
00:18:17,502 --> 00:18:18,114
Savage...

239
00:18:22,806 --> 00:18:23,306
Act.

240
00:18:27,805 --> 00:18:32,477
They call it civilized.

241
00:18:32,511 --> 00:18:34,679
There wasn't no civility to it.

242
00:18:42,189 --> 00:18:45,192
You won't scare me out of this.

243
00:18:50,401 --> 00:18:53,036
There ain't no worse way
to leave this world, Ruth.

244
00:18:56,976 --> 00:18:59,110
Burning alive is worse.

245
00:19:09,187 --> 00:19:12,555
I hated the sight of you

246
00:19:12,589 --> 00:19:16,322
when you came back to Cheyenne...

247
00:19:16,356 --> 00:19:19,827
The three of you.

248
00:19:19,861 --> 00:19:23,661
I got myself wound up so tight that day.

249
00:19:23,695 --> 00:19:27,966
I stormed out of the church

250
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:31,268
and trudged through the mud and the rain.

251
00:19:33,201 --> 00:19:35,936
And I saw your tent,

252
00:19:35,970 --> 00:19:40,643
and I was ready to say it all.

253
00:19:40,678 --> 00:19:42,912
But what you don't see

254
00:19:42,946 --> 00:19:45,813
when the anger grabs hold over you

255
00:19:45,848 --> 00:19:47,749
are puddles.

256
00:19:47,783 --> 00:19:52,289
Giant ones in the street.

257
00:19:52,324 --> 00:19:56,193
One wrong step, my feet slipped,

258
00:19:56,227 --> 00:19:59,232
and I fell hard into the mud.

259
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:03,267
[Chuckles]

260
00:20:03,301 --> 00:20:05,805
What I thought was mud,

261
00:20:05,839 --> 00:20:08,442
but then I smelled it.

262
00:20:08,476 --> 00:20:10,877
It was...

263
00:20:10,912 --> 00:20:13,779
Well, horse...

264
00:20:13,805 --> 00:20:15,540
Shit?

265
00:20:15,574 --> 00:20:18,809
[Laughing]

266
00:20:18,853 --> 00:20:21,254
It's not funny.

267
00:20:24,660 --> 00:20:26,228
Oh, what'd you do?

268
00:20:26,262 --> 00:20:27,530
What else could I do?

269
00:20:27,564 --> 00:20:29,832
I walked back through town.

270
00:20:29,866 --> 00:20:31,066
Covered in...

271
00:20:31,101 --> 00:20:33,135
[Laughter]

272
00:20:33,170 --> 00:20:37,575
No walk has felt so long in my life.

273
00:20:37,609 --> 00:20:40,379
When I got back, Ezra was there.

274
00:20:40,413 --> 00:20:42,883
You know what he said to me?

275
00:20:42,917 --> 00:20:45,683
[Laughing] "You smell like shit."

276
00:20:45,717 --> 00:20:47,419
[Laughs]

277
00:20:47,454 --> 00:20:48,421
Well...

278
00:20:48,455 --> 00:20:51,459
[Laughter]

279
00:20:53,127 --> 00:20:55,760
What did you tell him?

280
00:20:55,795 --> 00:20:58,064
I told him, "Don't say 'shit, '"

281
00:20:58,099 --> 00:21:00,469
and went and washed myself off.

282
00:21:06,076 --> 00:21:11,117
That was God answering my prayers.

283
00:21:14,326 --> 00:21:18,230
He was telling me I already
had a family of my own,

284
00:21:20,967 --> 00:21:23,470
Ezra and me.

285
00:21:28,310 --> 00:21:31,712
[Sighs]

286
00:21:31,746 --> 00:21:37,650
Still, I don't know

287
00:21:37,684 --> 00:21:41,353
why it took you so long to come see me.

288
00:21:43,922 --> 00:21:46,956
I didn't want you to explain.

289
00:21:46,991 --> 00:21:51,595
I just wanted to see you.

290
00:21:58,968 --> 00:22:03,435
I never thought you'd show
up at the church that night.

291
00:22:04,972 --> 00:22:07,375
[Sighs]

292
00:22:10,378 --> 00:22:13,380
I'll always show up, Ruth.

293
00:22:31,474 --> 00:22:33,207
Come on out here.

294
00:22:37,750 --> 00:22:39,718
Just to the window.

295
00:22:39,752 --> 00:22:41,452
Come on.

296
00:23:11,644 --> 00:23:13,748
This town needs their preacher.

297
00:23:28,297 --> 00:23:30,800
I'm nobody's preacher anymore.

298
00:23:48,020 --> 00:23:50,787
The hammering stopped.

299
00:23:50,821 --> 00:23:53,791
Mm.

300
00:23:53,825 --> 00:23:55,192
Hmm.

301
00:24:00,030 --> 00:24:02,830
They finished.

302
00:24:04,833 --> 00:24:08,270
Yeah.

303
00:24:08,304 --> 00:24:10,172
It's almost dawn.

304
00:24:20,720 --> 00:24:22,554
Yeah.

305
00:24:30,698 --> 00:24:34,169
Do you love me?

306
00:24:34,204 --> 00:24:36,039
Of course I do.

307
00:24:42,045 --> 00:24:43,781
But do you love me?

308
00:24:49,348 --> 00:24:51,684
I can't lose you, Ruth.

309
00:24:59,591 --> 00:25:01,425
I love you.

310
00:25:08,197 --> 00:25:10,732
I was a coward.

311
00:25:13,135 --> 00:25:15,302
I should've told you how I felt.

312
00:25:20,442 --> 00:25:24,976
I should've taken you and made you mine.

313
00:25:27,314 --> 00:25:30,149
The three of us could've been a family.

314
00:25:40,935 --> 00:25:43,139
Do you love her?

315
00:25:44,807 --> 00:25:47,041
It's all right. You can say.

316
00:25:47,076 --> 00:25:48,444
I don't know.

317
00:25:48,479 --> 00:25:52,879
You always know,

318
00:25:52,913 --> 00:25:55,417
deep down.

319
00:26:00,488 --> 00:26:02,423
I think I might.

320
00:26:09,029 --> 00:26:13,099
Go to her.

321
00:26:13,133 --> 00:26:17,600
Tell Naomi.

322
00:26:17,635 --> 00:26:20,134
I don't know if she'd have me.

323
00:26:22,169 --> 00:26:25,436
The brave choice is always family.

324
00:26:41,503 --> 00:26:43,806
Come on, get up.

325
00:26:43,841 --> 00:26:46,807
[Solemn music]

326
00:26:46,841 --> 00:26:47,341
♪ ♪

327
00:27:17,200 --> 00:27:20,201
[Footsteps]

328
00:27:21,903 --> 00:27:23,171
Cullen.

329
00:27:24,907 --> 00:27:26,341
[Gasps]

330
00:27:26,375 --> 00:27:30,110
Cullen.

331
00:27:34,550 --> 00:27:39,287
Mr. Bohannon, please step out of the cell.

332
00:27:39,321 --> 00:27:43,191
Just... just give us a minute.

333
00:27:43,225 --> 00:27:44,926
The law requires the death warrant

334
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:48,764
be read aloud the morning of the execution

335
00:27:48,798 --> 00:27:51,600
by the officer on duty.

336
00:27:51,635 --> 00:27:55,042
You asked for this role, Mr. Bohannon.

337
00:27:55,077 --> 00:27:56,712
I didn't ask for this.

338
00:27:56,747 --> 00:27:59,883
Badge on your chest says different.

339
00:28:07,164 --> 00:28:09,531
Miss Cole

340
00:28:09,566 --> 00:28:12,470
will accept her pardon now.

341
00:28:12,504 --> 00:28:14,773
Is that right, miss Cole?

342
00:28:18,943 --> 00:28:21,612
No, Mr. Campbell.

343
00:28:28,317 --> 00:28:30,251
I won't be party to this.

344
00:28:30,285 --> 00:28:33,254
Cullen.

345
00:28:33,289 --> 00:28:36,658
Cullen.

346
00:28:36,692 --> 00:28:40,126
Say you'll be there.

347
00:28:40,160 --> 00:28:42,298
Please.

348
00:28:53,109 --> 00:28:55,009
[Door opens and closes]

349
00:28:59,950 --> 00:29:02,453
13 coils,

350
00:29:02,487 --> 00:29:04,689
hemp, from St. Louis.

351
00:29:04,724 --> 00:29:07,327
It's the only kind I trust.

352
00:29:16,675 --> 00:29:18,509
Your hair, ma'am.

353
00:29:23,815 --> 00:29:25,716
- [Sniffs]
- It's the oil.

354
00:29:25,742 --> 00:29:28,978
Sees the knot don't catch.

355
00:29:29,020 --> 00:29:31,455
March you out five minutes before,

356
00:29:31,489 --> 00:29:33,857
exactly five minutes before.

357
00:29:37,160 --> 00:29:39,993
There will be a crowd.

358
00:29:40,028 --> 00:29:44,166
You don't got to worry. I'll be there.

359
00:29:44,201 --> 00:29:46,200
13 steps up to the platform

360
00:29:46,235 --> 00:29:49,635
where I'll tie your hands
and your feet first.

361
00:29:49,669 --> 00:29:51,136
Noose comes next.

362
00:29:51,171 --> 00:29:53,571
The hood is last.

363
00:29:57,106 --> 00:29:59,806
Will it hurt?

364
00:29:59,840 --> 00:30:02,073
Daddy never hung nobody before

365
00:30:02,108 --> 00:30:06,343
who come back to have it done over.

366
00:30:06,377 --> 00:30:10,015
You don't got to worry.

367
00:30:10,050 --> 00:30:11,849
I'll be there.

368
00:30:11,883 --> 00:30:13,416
[Sniffs]

369
00:30:16,622 --> 00:30:20,390
There's $50 in an account
in the Cheyenne bank

370
00:30:20,425 --> 00:30:23,493
and a pile of clothes at the laundry.

371
00:30:23,527 --> 00:30:27,727
See that they're donated to
the Council Bluffs mission.

372
00:30:27,761 --> 00:30:29,563
Wallace comes in to talk on Tuesdays.

373
00:30:29,598 --> 00:30:33,200
Someone should look in on him.

374
00:30:33,234 --> 00:30:36,234
Tomorrow's Tuesday.

375
00:30:40,473 --> 00:30:43,477
A pittance and some laundry.

376
00:30:46,780 --> 00:30:48,580
You're forgetting about
a city full of people

377
00:30:48,614 --> 00:30:52,218
who you've touched.

378
00:30:52,254 --> 00:30:56,088
You have my word they won't forget you.

379
00:30:56,123 --> 00:30:59,128
You're writing an article about me?

380
00:31:05,003 --> 00:31:06,402
Don't.

381
00:31:09,773 --> 00:31:13,243
It won't be remembered, and neither will we.

382
00:31:19,455 --> 00:31:21,191
It's time.

383
00:31:24,127 --> 00:31:26,964
Is there anything you need?

384
00:31:26,999 --> 00:31:28,833
Anything at all?

385
00:31:33,473 --> 00:31:37,509
Have you seen Mr. Bohannon?

386
00:31:37,544 --> 00:31:39,010
I haven't.

387
00:31:39,045 --> 00:31:40,011
But I can find him.

388
00:31:40,045 --> 00:31:43,514
No. Thank you.

389
00:31:43,549 --> 00:31:46,515
[Somber music]

390
00:31:46,549 --> 00:31:47,049
♪ ♪

391
00:32:18,242 --> 00:32:20,442
[Camera flash snaps]

392
00:32:20,476 --> 00:32:20,976
♪ ♪

393
00:32:51,774 --> 00:32:52,274
♪ ♪

394
00:33:27,309 --> 00:33:27,809
♪ ♪

395
00:34:02,812 --> 00:34:05,813
[Breathing unsteadily, sniffing]

396
00:34:31,641 --> 00:34:34,644
[Whimpering]

397
00:34:38,447 --> 00:34:40,482
Looser, please.

398
00:34:40,517 --> 00:34:43,018
No, ma'am.

399
00:35:03,180 --> 00:35:06,183
Wait!

400
00:35:06,217 --> 00:35:06,717
♪ ♪

401
00:35:22,933 --> 00:35:26,702
Any last words?

402
00:35:41,894 --> 00:35:44,864
[Sniffling]

403
00:35:44,898 --> 00:35:46,098
[Panting]

404
00:35:46,132 --> 00:35:48,099
[Fly buzzing]

405
00:35:48,134 --> 00:35:51,137
[Rope twisting]

406
00:35:52,538 --> 00:35:55,541
[Unsteady breathing]

407
00:35:57,577 --> 00:36:02,948
[Footsteps]

408
00:36:04,584 --> 00:36:10,286
[Heavy breathing]

409
00:36:14,692 --> 00:36:18,229
All aboard, train to Council Bluffs!

410
00:36:18,264 --> 00:36:20,398
All aboard!

411
00:36:20,433 --> 00:36:23,431
Final call!

412
00:36:32,032 --> 00:36:33,596
We're ready to escort miss Cole's body

413
00:36:33,633 --> 00:36:36,063
to the Council Bluffs Mission.

414
00:36:36,098 --> 00:36:38,967
Buried her this morning.

415
00:36:39,001 --> 00:36:40,833
She's with her son.

416
00:36:45,708 --> 00:36:48,275
God hasn't given up on this place yet.

417
00:36:51,549 --> 00:36:53,382
This wasn't God's doing.

418
00:37:04,795 --> 00:37:07,765
"The railroad may be America's dream,

419
00:37:07,799 --> 00:37:11,437
"but what's left behind in
Governor Campbell's Cheyenne

420
00:37:11,471 --> 00:37:15,708
is a nightmare."

421
00:37:15,742 --> 00:37:19,414
This is how you see Cheyenne?

422
00:37:19,448 --> 00:37:21,884
I told you you weren't going to like it.

423
00:37:21,919 --> 00:37:24,720
I thought we shared a vision

424
00:37:24,754 --> 00:37:27,921
for what this city could be.

425
00:37:27,955 --> 00:37:29,153
The only vision that I have is

426
00:37:29,186 --> 00:37:32,222
a poor girl swinging from a rope.

427
00:37:32,257 --> 00:37:35,557
What befell miss Cole was a tragedy,

428
00:37:35,591 --> 00:37:39,292
but printing this won't bring her back.

429
00:37:39,326 --> 00:37:41,593
The governor controls a great many things.

430
00:37:41,627 --> 00:37:42,927
The press is not one of them.

431
00:37:42,961 --> 00:37:46,162
I'm not asking you as governor.

432
00:37:51,132 --> 00:37:54,937
I've always been a terrible dance partner.

433
00:37:54,971 --> 00:37:56,839
By this time next week,

434
00:37:56,873 --> 00:37:59,575
you'll be back covering America's dream,
having authored

435
00:37:59,609 --> 00:38:03,278
nothing substantial but
the end of a relationship.

436
00:38:07,017 --> 00:38:09,887
This is far more important, John.

437
00:38:20,900 --> 00:38:24,638
In your nightmare, I'm a monster?

438
00:38:36,257 --> 00:38:38,191
Enjoy your ashes.

439
00:38:53,581 --> 00:38:55,679
Everybody back out of the way.

440
00:39:02,115 --> 00:39:05,116
[Steam hissing]

441
00:39:07,584 --> 00:39:12,592
[Metal clicking]

442
00:39:55,336 --> 00:39:59,107
The pressure's too high.

443
00:41:07,148 --> 00:41:08,348
Yeah!

444
00:41:08,382 --> 00:41:09,615
[All cheering]

445
00:41:09,650 --> 00:41:12,451
All right. All right.

446
00:41:14,788 --> 00:41:16,521
All right,

447
00:41:16,555 --> 00:41:18,956
y'all quit your yapping
and get back to work.

448
00:41:18,990 --> 00:41:21,991
Heard the man. Back to work.

449
00:41:36,449 --> 00:41:39,454
[Reverberating din]

450
00:42:00,949 --> 00:42:02,869
I'm afraid the champagne and cigars

451
00:42:02,883 --> 00:42:06,017
will have to wait until
we've taken the summit.

452
00:42:06,052 --> 00:42:09,454
Send for 300 workers from Omaha to lay track

453
00:42:09,488 --> 00:42:12,756
and two trainloads of lumber from Chicago.

454
00:42:12,791 --> 00:42:18,696
Oh, and throw up a wire to general Grant.

455
00:42:18,730 --> 00:42:21,631
Tell him we'll summit before month's end.

456
00:42:27,836 --> 00:42:31,103
Well, what is it, Bohannon?

457
00:42:37,108 --> 00:42:39,142
I quit.

